#: index.docbook:2
msgid "&kppp; and security issues"
msgstr "&kppp; in vprašanja varnosti"

#: index.docbook:4
msgid ""
"This section is mainly for superusers (<systemitem>root</systemitem>"
") people with high security demands, or simply technically interested "
"people. It is not necessary to read this if you only use &Linux; at home for "
"yourself, although you may learn a thing or two in any case."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek je v glavnem za superuporabnike (<systemitem>root</systemitem>"
"), ljudi s pomembnimi varnostnimi vprašanji ali za preprosto tehnično "
"zainteresirane ljudi. Ni vam potrebno prebrati tega, če uporabljate &Linux; "
"samo doma za vaše potrebe (čeprav se lahko naučite kaj novega, če to "
"preberete)."

#: index.docbook:10
msgid "Restricting access to &kppp;"
msgstr "Omejevanje dostopa do &kppp;"

#: index.docbook:12
msgid ""
"A system administrator might want to restrict access as to who is allowed to "
"use &kppp;. There are two ways to accomplish this."
msgstr ""
"Sistemski administrator bo mogoče želel omejiti dostop, komu je dovoljeno "
"uporabljati &kppp;. Za to obstajata dva načina:"

#: index.docbook:16
msgid "Restricting access with group permissions"
msgstr "Omejevanje dostopa z dovoljenji za skupine"

#: index.docbook:18
msgid ""
"Create a new group (you might want to name it "
"<systemitem>dialout</systemitem>"
" or similar), and put every user that should be allowed to use &kppp; into "
"that group. Then type at the prompt:"
msgstr ""
"Ustvarite novo skupino (mogoče jo boste hoteli poimenovati "
"<systemitem>dialout</systemitem> ali podobno), dodajte vse uporabnike, ki "
"naj bi imeli dovoljenje za uporabo &kppp;-ja v to skupino in vtipkajte:"

#: index.docbook:22
msgid ""
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>chown</command> "
"<option>root.dialout</option> "
"<filename>/opt/kde/bin/kppp</filename></userinput>\n"
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>chmod</command> <option>4750</option>"
" <filename>/opt/kde/bin/kppp</filename></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>chown</command> "
"<option>root.dialout</option> "
"<filename>/opt/kde/bin/kppp</filename></userinput>\n"
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>chmod</command> <option>4750</option>"
" <filename>/opt/kde/bin/kppp</filename></userinput>"

#: index.docbook:26
msgid ""
"This assumes that &kde; was installed in <filename class=\"directory\"> "
"/opt/kde/</filename> and that your new group is named "
"<systemitem>dialout</systemitem>."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj se privzame, da je bil &kde; nameščen v </filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/local/kde</filename>in vaša nova skupina se "
"imenuje <systemitem>dialout</systemitem>."

#: index.docbook:33
msgid "Restricting access &kppp;'s way"
msgstr "Omejevanje dostopa na &kppp;-jev način"

#: index.docbook:35
msgid ""
"Before doing anything, &kppp; checks if there is a file named "
"<filename>/etc/kppp.allow</filename>. If such a file exists, only users "
"named in this file are allowed to dial out. This file must be readable by "
"everyone (but of course <emphasis>NOT</emphasis>"
" writable.) Only login names are recognized, so you cannot use "
"<acronym>UID</acronym>'s in this file. Here is a short example:"
msgstr ""
"Preden se karkoli naredi, &kppp; preveri, če obstaja datoteka imenovana "
"<filename>/etc/kppp.allow</filename>. Če ta datoteka obstaja, bodo SAMO "
"uporabniki imenovani v tej datoteki imeli dovoljenje za klicanje. Ta "
"datoteka mora biti berljiva vsakemu uporabniku (seveda "
"<emphasis>NE</emphasis> zapisljiva). Prepoznana so samo imena s katerimi se "
"uporabniki prijavijo, zato ne morete uporabiti <acronym>UID</acronym>-jev v "
"tej datoteki. Tukaj je kratek primer:"

#: index.docbook:42
msgid ""
"# /etc/kppp.allow\n"
"# comment lines like this are ignored\n"
"# as well as empty lines\n"
"\n"
"fred\n"
"karl\n"
"daisy"
msgstr ""
"# /etc/kppp.allow\n"
"# comment lines like this are ignored\n"
"# as well as empty lines\n"
"\n"
"fred\n"
"karl\n"
"daisy"

#: index.docbook:52
msgid ""
"In the example above, only the users <systemitem>fred</systemitem>, "
"<systemitem>karl</systemitem> and <systemitem>daisy</systemitem>"
" are allowed to dial out, as well as every user with a "
"<acronym>UID</acronym> of 0 (so you don't have to explicitly list root in "
"the file)."
msgstr ""
"V zgornjem primeru samo uporabniki <systemitem>fred</systemitem>, "
"<systemitem>karl</systemitem> in <systemitem>daisy</systemitem> lahko "
"kličejo, kot tudi vsak uporabnik z <acronym>UID</acronym> nastavljen na 0. "
"Zato vam ni potrebno postaviti uporabnika root v to datoteko."

#: index.docbook:62
msgid "&kppp; has the <acronym>SUID</acronym> bit on? What about security?"
msgstr "&kppp; ima nastavljen <acronym>SUID</acronym> bit. Kaj pa varnost?"

#: index.docbook:65
msgid ""
"It's virtually impossible to write a dialler without the "
"<acronym>SUID</acronym> bit that is both safe and easy to use for "
"inexperienced users. &kppp; addresses the security issues with the following "
"strategy."
msgstr ""
"Navidezno je nemogoče napisati program za klicanje brez "
"<acronym>SUID</acronym> bita, ki je istočasno varen in preprost za uporabo "
"za neizkušene uporabnike. &kppp; odgovarja na varnostna vprašanja z "
"naslednjo strategijo:"

#: index.docbook:69
msgid "Immediately after the program starts, &kppp; forks."
msgstr "Takoj ko se program zažene, se &kppp; razveji."

#: index.docbook:69
msgid ""
"The master process, which handles all the <acronym>GUI</acronym> stuff such "
"as user interaction) drops the <acronym>SUID</acronym>"
" state after the fork, and runs with normal user privileges."
msgstr ""
"Glavni proces (master process) (kateri skrbi za vse <acronym>GUI</acronym> "
"stvari, uporabniško medsebojno delovanje in podobno) takoj za tem prekine "
"<acronym>SUID</acronym> način in teče z navadnimi uporabniškimi "
"privilegiji."

#: index.docbook:69
msgid ""
"The slave process keeps its privileges, and is responsible for all actions "
"that need <systemitem>root</systemitem> privileges. To keep this part safe, "
"no &kde; or &Qt; library calls are used here, just simple library calls. The "
"source code for this process is short (around 500 lines) and well "
"documented, so it's easy for you to check it for security holes."
msgstr ""
"Podrejeni proces (slave process) ohrani svoje privilegije in je odgovoren za "
"akcije, ki potrebujejo privilegije <systemitem>root</systemitem>-a. Da "
"ohranimo ta del varen, se tukaj ne uporabijo nobeni klici &kde; ali &Qt "
"knjižnic, ampak samo preprosti klici C knjižnic. Izvorna koda za ta proces "
"je kratka (okrog 500 vrstic) in dobro dokumentirana, zato jo je lahko "
"preveriti, če vsebuje varnostne luknje."

#: index.docbook:69
msgid ""
"Master and slave processes communicate with standard &UNIX; "
"<acronym>IPC</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Glavni in podrejeni proces komunicirata s standardnim &UNIX; "
"<acronym>IPC</acronym>."

